Spatial cell clustering of Xenium data by MEcell

Qi Liu

19 June, 2025

  • Load the library and the seurat object
  • Build the microenvironment-aware SNN graph (named MEcell), followed by clustering
  • heart and thymus, inner and outer ear

Load the library and the seurat object

library(MEcell)
library(ggplot2)

# The data have already been log-normalized, scaled and RunPCA using Seurat
#The Seurat object contains raw counts,normalized data, and PCA embeddings

obj<-readRDS(url("https://www.dropbox.com/scl/fi/oblnyz6at37vwplxm04g4/xenium_mousepup.rds?rlkey=uoxti44uy5up9ib3jygeqcunm&dl=1"))

Build the microenvironment-aware SNN graph (named MEcell), followed by clustering

# build the microenvironment-aware SNN graph (named MEcell)

obj<-MEcell(obj)

#clustering on the MEcell SNN graph
obj<-FindClusters(obj,graph.name = "MEcell",verbose = F)

#visualizing cell clustering 
ImageDimPlot(obj,group.by="MEcell_res.0.8")+ ggtitle("MEcell clustering")+theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5))

heart and thymus, inner and outer ear

#heart (cluster 33) and thymus (cluster 34)
#Cluster 9 represents the outermost skin layer in the mouse pup
ImageDimPlot(obj[,obj$MEcell_res.0.8 %in% c(9,33,34)])+ ggtitle("heart and thymus")+theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5))

ImageFeaturePlot(obj[,obj$MEcell_res.0.8 %in% c(9,33,34)],features =c("Pln","Arpp21"))

#inner (cluster 23) and outer ear (cluster 26) 
ImageDimPlot(obj[,obj$MEcell_res.0.8 %in% c(9,23,26)])+ ggtitle("inner and outer ear")+theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5))

ImageFeaturePlot(obj[,obj$MEcell_res.0.8 %in% c(9,23,26)],features =c("Otor","Comp"))
